d":"289","parent":"285","text":"Red de apoyo identificada","guid":"jq7xUXJhRBi1Pb1_oNNeng","children":[]},{"id":"290","parent":"285","text":"Derivación a ambulatorio para AUD","guid":"m8HWE9LhRAmhBO5F5LAVug","children":[]}]},{"id":"291","parent":"270","text":"Tratamiento del AUD post-alta","guid":"5LsKib7jTo6wdocH4MzIGg","children":[{"id":"292","parent":"291","text":"Naltrexona → precaución en hepatopatía severa","guid":"Bnn8ZkYLT0O8Y9Wyk6pu4Q","children":[]},{"id":"293","parent":"291","text":"Acamprosato → ajustar por ClCr (evitar si <30)","guid":"AHLpBJJxQ2yGCxfsK3IC1A","children":[]},{"id":"294","parent":"291","text":"Disulfiram → NO recomendado en AM (riesgo CV alto)","guid":"4NmIPHTdQaK-F0ID4cOZWw","children":[]},{"id":"295","parent":"291","text":"Terapia psicosocial, grupos de apoyo","guid":"z6_7tJ04RaWmlOaYu_wGWg","children":[]},{"id":"296","parent":"291","text":"STOPP criterio: revisar fármacos que interactúan","guid":"5uNGS-fKTyCpxyQQok6XRg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"297","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"EEPraD28Si-hE9Oo981kAQ","children":[{"id":"298","parent":"297","text":"TIAMINA SIEMPRE antes de glucosa → regla de oro","guid":"-R74rcWYROOGKNkj3PRXkA","children":[]},{"id":"299","parent":"297","text":"CIWA-Ar NO validado en AM con DCL → usar juicio clínico y escalas alternativas","guid":"Lr1lnt1tQvar7-b052k7DA","children":[]},{"id":"300","parent":"297","text":"LORAZEPAM > diazepam en AM (sin metabolito activo, glucuronidación hepática)","guid":"AD6kG89zTX2GtErzN7p2tw","children":[]},{"id":"301","parent":"297","text":"Haloperidol NO es primera línea → baja umbral convulsivo","guid":"EHF6e9G9Ty-SkRMWu0U4PQ","children":[]},{"id":"302","parent":"297","text":"Dexmedetomidina es ADYUVANTE en UCI → NO reemplaza benzodiacepinas","guid":"DDopZpobTn26axfC7IooPg","children":[]},{"id":"303","parent":"297","text":"\"Start low, go slow, but go\" → titular con dosis bajas pero NO subtratar","guid":"tdlwwA__QDSb6tjD2wwWUA","children":[]},{"id":"304","parent":"297","text":"AWS puede debutar TARDÍAMENTE en AM (72-96h) → mantener vigilancia","guid":"j9WIuKx8THajxe4OOTCzKA","children":[]},{"id":"305","parent":"297","text":"Caída + confusión + OH → PEDIR TC cerebro siempre (HSD)","guid":"-DDSxxPsQQmCK40-T3BgAw","children":[]},{"id":"306","parent":"297","text":"Alcoholemia normal NO descarta AWS en gran bebedor","guid":"oyYKxdGSTkSPy9SbD32jCg","children":[]},{"id":"307","parent":"297","text":"Esquema SYMPTOM-TRIGGERED reduce dosis acumulada pero REQUIERE CIWA confiable","guid":"3wU5bOyiQPSJNDahX1cUgg","children":[]},{"id":"308","parent":"297","text":"En DCL usar FIXED-SCHEDULE con rescate","guid":"RZCZ4V9YTQiwnxNXEeRvWA","children":[]},{"id":"309","parent":"297","text":"HipoMg precipita convulsiones y arritmias → reponer agresivamente","guid":"l5LuQLznToOxL8siDKc02g","children":[]},{"id":"310","parent":"297","text":"Efecto KINDLING → cada episodio aumenta severidad del siguiente","guid":"kK9ZSyOpTqK-CN3b5n-nhQ","children":[]},{"id":"311","parent":"297","text":"Mortalidad del DT en AM 2-5x mayor → baja tolerancia para UCI","guid":"wH3_q9yaRSSitKlEGW_CZg","children":[]},{"id":"312","parent":"297","text":"EVITAR clordiazepóxido y diazepam en AM (acumulación, delirium)","guid":"Okgwd8dfSjiYBUB-ICw3gQ","children":[]},{"id":"313","parent":"297","text":"PAWSS ≥4 al ingreso → iniciar profilaxis farmacológica precoz","guid":"vFtRH_vLSFqPRvhDufjQUQ","children":[]},{"id":"314","parent":"297","text":"Referencias","guid":"r0pFh3BuQWO4S-uD-45O6A","children":[{"id":"315","parent":"314","text":"1. Day E, Daly C. Clinical management of the alcohol withdrawal syndrome. Addiction. 2022;117(3):804-814.","guid":"2bY5gcbPQ2iMtufP8510NQ","children":[]},{"id":"316","parent":"314","text":"2. Wood E, Albarqouni L, Tkachuk S, et al. Will This Hospitalized Patient Develop Severe Alcohol Withdrawal Syndrome? The Rational Clinical Examination. JAMA. 2018;320(8):825-833.","guid":"tAtw9A7MSEagiqJfKy-6mA","children":[]},{"id":"317","parent":"314","text":"3. 